top-mode.el can run the unix programm "<tt>top</tt>" from Emacs.

You can find it here: Lisp:top-mode.el

=== Installation ===

Load it with <tt>auoload</tt> or <tt>require</tt>.
The enter

 M-x top-mode

or load it permanently with

 (top-mode 1)

in your emacs configuration file.

=== Usage ===

Press <tt>g</tt> to run top and <tt>q</tt> to quit.
Other features are:

* strace a process
* kill processes
* renice processes
